Block copy and paste
--------------------
1. Cut and paste:
-----------------
Position the cursor where you want to begin cutting.
Press v to select characters (or uppercase V to select whole lines).
Move the cursor to the end of what you want to cut.
Press d to cut (or y to copy).
Move to where you would like to paste.
Press P to paste before the cursor, or p to paste after.

d = delete = cut
y = yank = copy
----------------

2. Copy from one file to another
---------------------------------
1. Edit the first file, yanking the text you want. Then open your second file from within vi (:e /path/to/other/file) and paste it
2. Open both files together in a split window and navigate between them using Ctrl + w, Up/Down either by: 

i)  vi -o /path/to/file1 /path/to/file2
ii) From within the first file, Ctrl + w, s
